    • Constructor Detail

      • CodeMethod

        public CodeMethod​(java.lang.String name,
                  CodeParent parent,
                  CodeParameter returnType,
                  boolean hasMultiplicity,
                  CodeVisibility visibility,
                  boolean isAbstract,
                  boolean isStatic,
                  boolean isFinal)
        Constructor with name, CodeParent, return type, value whether the return value has a multiplicity and modifiers. The modifiers are converted to an int value usable for the CodeModifier methods.
        Initializes the lists for CodeParameters, CodeTemplateBindings and CodeTemplateParameters
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the method
        parent - the CodeParent element of the method
        returnType - the CodeParameter representing the return type of the method
        hasMultiplicity - true if the field has a multiplicity
        visibility - the CodeVisibility value representing the access modifier of the method
        isAbstract - determines whether the method is abstract
        isStatic - determines whether the method is static
        isFinal - determines whether the method is final
